---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Diagram Pipeline"
  description="Chain a diagram from image to Mermaid to draw.io to an Excel flow register — hops, applications, interfaces, and a manual app→database→platform reference."
  mainClass="max-w-5xl"
>
  <article class="tool">
    <header class="thead">
      <p class="kick">Tools · Extract &amp; Analyze</p>
      <h1>Diagram Pipeline</h1>
      <p class="sub">
        One chain, four steps: a picture of a diagram → editable <strong>Mermaid</strong> →
        a <strong>draw.io</strong> file → an <strong>Excel flow register</strong> of every hop
        (from &amp; to application, interface mechanism) joined to a manual
        application → database → platform reference.
      </p>
      <a class="back" href="/tools/">Back to all tools</a>
    </header>

    <!-- STEP 1 — INPUT -->
    <section class="step">
      <h2 class="step-h"><span class="n">1</span> Input — image or Mermaid</h2>
      <p class="hint">
        Upload a diagram image to convert it with vision AI (sent to the AI service), or skip
        straight to step 2 by pasting Mermaid below.
      </p>
      <div class="drop" id="drop">
        <input type="file" id="file" accept="image/png,image/jpeg,image/webp,image/gif,image/svg+xml,.svg" />
        <div class="dl">Select a diagram image</div>
        <div class="ds">PNG, JPG, WebP, GIF, or SVG (≤ 6 MB). Mermaid / draw.io SVGs are read directly (lossless); other SVGs are rasterised for vision AI.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="preview-img" id="previmg" hidden><img id="thumb" alt="upload preview" /></div>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="btn primary" id="go" disabled>Convert image → Mermaid</button>
        <span class="status" id="status">Select an image, or paste Mermaid in step 2.</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 2 — MERMAID -->
    <section class="step">
      <h2 class="step-h"><span class="n">2</span> Mermaid <span class="muted2">— edit, then render</span></h2>
      <div class="grid2">
        <div class="col">
          <div class="row tight">
            <button class="btn sm" id="render">↻ Render</button>
            <button class="btn sm" id="copyM">Copy</button>
            <button class="btn sm" id="dlM">Download .mmd</button>
            <button class="btn sm" id="sample">Load sample</button>
          </div>
          <textarea id="code" class="code" spellcheck="false" placeholder="flowchart TD&#10;  A[App A] --> B[App B]"></textarea>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
          <h3 class="sub-h">Preview</h3>
          <div id="preview" class="preview"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 3 — DRAW.IO -->
    <section class="step">
      <h2 class="step-h"><span class="n">3</span> draw.io <span class="muted2">— generated from the Mermaid above</span></h2>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="btn primary" id="genDrawio">Generate draw.io</button>
        <label class="field-inline">
          <span>Colours</span>
          <select id="scheme">
            <option value="archimate">ArchiMate</option>
            <option value="togaf">TOGAF</option>
            <option value="azure">Azure</option>
            <option value="none">None</option>
          </select>
        </label>
        <button class="btn" id="dlDrawio" disabled>Download .drawio</button>
        <button class="btn" id="openDrawio" disabled>Open in diagrams.net ↗</button>
        <button class="btn" id="copyDrawio" disabled>Copy XML</button>
        <span class="status" id="statusD"></span>
      </div>
      <p class="hint">
        Layout is a simple layered placement — open it in diagrams.net and run
        <em>Arrange → Layout</em> for an auto-tidy. Shapes follow the Mermaid (databases
        <code>[(…)]</code> become cylinders); colours are applied by inferred node type
        (set types in step 4). The Mermaid itself stays faithful to the source.
      </p>
      <textarea id="drawioXml" class="code mono-sm" spellcheck="false" placeholder="Generated draw.io XML appears here." hidden></textarea>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 4 — FLOW REGISTER -->
    <section class="step">
      <h2 class="step-h"><span class="n">4</span> Flow register → Excel</h2>
      <p class="hint">
        Each <strong>hop</strong> (one connection) becomes a row: from node, interface mechanism
        (the edge label), to node. Not every box is an application — diagrams often include
        strategies, objectives, people, or projects. Set each node's <strong>type</strong> below
        (auto-classified from its swimlane) so the export tags <code>From Type</code> /
        <code>To Type</code>, and add a <strong>database</strong> / <strong>technology platform</strong>
        where it applies. Saved in your browser and joined into the export.
      </p>

      <div class="ref-head">
        <h3 class="sub-h">Node reference <span class="muted2" id="refCount"></span></h3>
        <div class="row tight">
          <button class="btn sm" id="seedRef">Sync nodes from diagram</button>
          <button class="btn sm" id="addRow">+ Row</button>
          <label class="btn sm filelbl">Import CSV<input type="file" id="refCsv" accept=".csv,text/csv" hidden /></label>
          <button class="btn sm" id="exportRefCsv">Export CSV</button>
          <button class="btn sm danger" id="clearRef">Clear</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table class="ref" id="refTable">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Node</th><th>Type</th><th>Database</th><th>Technology platform</th><th aria-label="remove"></th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody id="refBody"></tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="row export-row">
        <button class="btn primary" id="exportXlsx">Export Excel (.xlsx)</button>
        <label class="chk"><input type="checkbox" id="optChains" checked /> Include end-to-end chains sheet</label>
        <span class="status" id="statusX"></span>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    /* ============================================================
       Diagram Pipeline — all client-side except the image→Mermaid
       call (which reuses the existing EA Explorer worker endpoint).
       Core parser/layout/drawio/register logic is unit-tested in
       Node (see commit notes) before being inlined here.
       ============================================================ */
    const $ = (id) => document.getElementById(id);
    const WORKER = 'https://ea-explorer-worker.sfrancis2017.workers.dev';
    const REF_KEY = 'diagram-pipeline:ref';
    let file = null, _mermaid = null, lastXml = '', drawioScheme = 'archimate', typeLookup = {};

    async function mermaidLib() {
      if (!_mermaid) {
        _mermaid = (await import('https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid@11/dist/mermaid.esm.min.mjs')).default;
        _mermaid.initialize({ startOnLoad: false, securityLevel: 'loose', theme: 'default' });
      }
      return _mermaid;
    }

    // ---------- Mermaid flowchart parser ----------
    const SHAPE_WRAPPERS = [
      { open: '([', close: '])', shape: 'stadium' },
      { open: '[[', close: ']]', shape: 'subroutine' },
      { open: '[(', close: ')]', shape: 'cylinder' },
      { open: '((', close: '))', shape: 'circle' },
      { open: '{{', close: '}}', shape: 'hexagon' },
      { open: '[', close: ']', shape: 'rect' },
      { open: '(', close: ')', shape: 'round' },
      { open: '{', close: '}', shape: 'diamond' },
      { open: '>', close: ']', shape: 'flag' },
    ];
    function stripQuotes(s) {
      s = s.trim();
      if ((s.startsWith('"') && s.endsWith('"')) || (s.startsWith("'") && s.endsWith("'"))) s = s.slice(1, -1);
      return s.replace(/<br\s*\/?>/gi, ' ').replace(/&amp;/g, '&').replace(/&lt;/g, '<').replace(/&gt;/g, '>').trim();
    }
    function readNode(str, i) {
      while (i < str.length && /\s/.test(str[i])) i++;
      const idMatch = /^[A-Za-z0-9_.]+/.exec(str.slice(i));
      if (!idMatch) return null;
      const id = idMatch[0];
      let j = i + id.length, label = id, shape = 'rect';
      for (const w of SHAPE_WRAPPERS) {
        if (str.startsWith(w.open, j)) {
          const end = str.indexOf(w.close, j + w.open.length);
          if (end !== -1) { label = stripQuotes(str.slice(j + w.open.length, end)); shape = w.shape; j = end + w.close.length; break; }
        }
      }
      return { id, label, shape, next: j };
    }
    function normaliseInlineLabels(line) {
      return line
        .replace(/--\s+([^>\n|]+?)\s+-->/g, '-->|$1|')
        .replace(/==\s+([^>\n|]+?)\s+==>/g, '==>|$1|')
        .replace(/-\.\s+([^>\n|]+?)\s+\.->/g, '-.->|$1|');
    }
    function readLink(str, i) {
      while (i < str.length && /\s/.test(str[i])) i++;
      const m = /^([ox<]?[-.=]{1,}[-.=ox>]*[->ox]?)/.exec(str.slice(i));
      if (!m) return null;
      let j = i + m[0].length, label = '';
      const rest = str.slice(j).replace(/^\s+/, '');
      if (rest.startsWith('|')) {
        const consumedWs = str.slice(j).length - rest.length;
        const end = rest.indexOf('|', 1);
        if (end !== -1) { label = stripQuotes(rest.slice(1, end)); j = j + consumedWs + end + 1; }
      }
      return { label, next: j };
    }
    function parseMermaid(code) {
      const nodes = new Map(), edges = [];
      let direction = 'TD', started = false;
      const subgraphStack = [];
      const addNode = (n) => {
        if (!nodes.has(n.id)) nodes.set(n.id, { id: n.id, label: n.label, shape: n.shape, group: '' });
        else { const ex = nodes.get(n.id); if (n.label && n.label !== n.id && ex.label === ex.id) { ex.label = n.label; ex.shape = n.shape; } }
        if (subgraphStack.length) { const stored = nodes.get(n.id); if (!stored.group) stored.group = subgraphStack[subgraphStack.length - 1]; }
      };
      for (let raw of code.split('\n')) {
        let line = raw.replace(/%%.*$/, '').trim();
        if (!line) continue;
        const head = /^(?:flowchart|graph)\s+(TB|TD|BT|RL|LR)?/i.exec(line);
        if (head && !started) {
          started = true;
          if (head[1]) direction = head[1].toUpperCase() === 'TB' ? 'TD' : head[1].toUpperCase();
          line = line.slice(head[0].length).trim();
          if (!line) continue;
        }
        const sg = /^subgraph\s+(.*)$/i.exec(line);
        if (sg) {
          let title = sg[1].trim();
          const tm = /\[(.*?)\]/.exec(title);
          title = tm ? stripQuotes(tm[1]) : stripQuotes(title.replace(/^["']|["']$/g, ''));
          subgraphStack.push(title || 'Group');
          continue;
        }
        if (/^end$/i.test(line)) { subgraphStack.pop(); continue; }
        if (/^(style|classDef|class|click|linkStyle|direction)\b/i.test(line)) continue;
        line = normaliseInlineLabels(line);
        let i = 0, prev = readNode(line, i);
        if (!prev) continue;
        addNode(prev); i = prev.next;
        let guard = 0;
        while (i < line.length && guard++ < 200) {
          const link = readLink(line, i);
          if (!link) break;
          const node = readNode(line, link.next);
          if (!node) break;
          addNode(node);
          edges.push({ from: prev.id, to: node.id, label: link.label });
          prev = node; i = node.next;
        }
      }
      return { direction, nodes, edges };
    }

    // ---------- Node type inference ----------
    // Swimlane (subgraph) membership is the strongest signal; then shape; then
    // label keywords. Lets the register tag what's an application vs a strategy,
    // objective, person, etc. — without narrowing the faithful AI extraction.
    const NODE_TYPES = ['Application', 'Database', 'Platform', 'Strategy/Objective', 'Actor/External', 'Process/Other'];
    function inferType(node) {
      const g = (node.group || '').toLowerCase();
      if (g) {
        if (/strateg|objective|goal|outcome|driver|vision|mission|kpi|capabilit|principle|value/.test(g)) return 'Strategy/Objective';
        if (/data|database|datastore|data ?store/.test(g)) return 'Database';
        if (/tech|platform|infrastructure|hosting|node/.test(g)) return 'Platform';
        if (/person|people|actor|role|stakeholder|team|user|organi[sz]ation|business unit/.test(g)) return 'Actor/External';
        if (/project|initiative|programme|program|work ?package|process|business|function/.test(g)) return 'Process/Other';
        if (/applicat|system|software|service|app\b/.test(g)) return 'Application';
      }
      if (node.shape === 'cylinder') return 'Database';
      const l = (node.label || '').toLowerCase();
      if (/^(increase|reduce|improve|grow|diversif|enhance|succeed|expand|maximi[sz]e|minimi[sz]e)\b/.test(l)
          || /strateg|objective|\bgoal\b|\bvision\b|\bmission\b|\bkpi\b/.test(l)) return 'Strategy/Objective';
      return 'Application';
    }

    // ---------- Layered layout (cycle-safe) ----------
    function layout(graph) {
      const { nodes, edges, direction } = graph;
      const ids = [...nodes.keys()];
      const preds = new Map(ids.map((id) => [id, []]));
      for (const e of edges) { if (nodes.has(e.from) && nodes.has(e.to)) preds.get(e.to).push(e.from); }
      const rank = new Map(), onStack = new Set();
      const rankOf = (id) => {
        if (rank.has(id)) return rank.get(id);
        if (onStack.has(id)) return 0;
        onStack.add(id);
        let r = 0;
        for (const p of preds.get(id) || []) r = Math.max(r, rankOf(p) + 1);
        onStack.delete(id); rank.set(id, r); return r;
      };
      for (const id of ids) rankOf(id);
      const byRank = new Map();
      for (const id of ids) { const r = rank.get(id); if (!byRank.has(r)) byRank.set(r, []); byRank.get(r).push(id); }
      const NW = 170, NH = 60, GX = 80, GY = 60;
      const horizontal = direction === 'LR' || direction === 'RL';
      const pos = new Map();
      for (const [r, list] of byRank) {
        list.forEach((id, idx) => {
          const along = idx * (horizontal ? (NH + GY) : (NW + GX));
          const across = r * (horizontal ? (NW + GX) : (NH + GY));
          pos.set(id, { x: (horizontal ? across : along) + 40, y: (horizontal ? along : across) + 40, w: NW, h: NH });
        });
      }
      return pos;
    }

    // ---------- draw.io XML ----------
    const SHAPE_STYLE = {
      rect: 'rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;',
      round: 'rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;',
      stadium: 'rounded=1;arcSize=40;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;',
      subroutine: 'shape=process;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;',
      cylinder: 'shape=cylinder3;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;boundedLbl=1;backgroundOutline=1;',
      circle: 'ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;',
      hexagon: 'shape=hexagon;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;',
      diamond: 'rhombus;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;',
      flag: 'shape=card;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;',
    };
    function xmlEscape(s) { return String(s).replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/</g, '&lt;').replace(/>/g, '&gt;').replace(/"/g, '&quot;'); }
    // Colour schemes — applied to draw.io by inferred node type, so the export
    // reads like an architecture diagram. Mermaid stays faithful to the source.
    const PALETTES = {
      archimate: {
        'Application': { fill: '#dae8fc', stroke: '#6c8ebf' }, 'Strategy/Objective': { fill: '#ffe6cc', stroke: '#d79b00' },
        'Actor/External': { fill: '#fff2cc', stroke: '#d6b656' }, 'Process/Other': { fill: '#d5e8d4', stroke: '#82b366' },
        'Database': { fill: '#dae8fc', stroke: '#6c8ebf' }, 'Platform': { fill: '#d5e8d4', stroke: '#82b366' },
      },
      togaf: {
        'Application': { fill: '#cfe2f3', stroke: '#3d85c6' }, 'Strategy/Objective': { fill: '#fce5cd', stroke: '#e69138' },
        'Actor/External': { fill: '#fff2cc', stroke: '#f1c232' }, 'Process/Other': { fill: '#d9ead3', stroke: '#6aa84f' },
        'Database': { fill: '#d0e0e3', stroke: '#45818e' }, 'Platform': { fill: '#d9d2e9', stroke: '#674ea7' },
      },
      azure: {
        'Application': { fill: '#cce4f6', stroke: '#0078d4' }, 'Strategy/Objective': { fill: '#e6e6fa', stroke: '#5c2d91' },
        'Actor/External': { fill: '#e1f0da', stroke: '#107c10' }, 'Process/Other': { fill: '#fff4ce', stroke: '#ffb900' },
        'Database': { fill: '#cce4f6', stroke: '#0078d4' }, 'Platform': { fill: '#deecf9', stroke: '#005ba1' },
      },
    };
    function drawioStyleFor(n) {
      let style = SHAPE_STYLE[n.shape] || SHAPE_STYLE.rect;
      const t = typeLookup[n.label.toLowerCase().trim()] || inferType(n); // grid override wins
      const p = PALETTES[drawioScheme]; const c = p && p[t];
      if (c) style += `fillColor=${c.fill};strokeColor=${c.stroke};`;
      return style;
    }
    function toDrawio(graph, pos) {
      const { nodes, edges } = graph;
      const cells = [];
      for (const [id, n] of nodes) {
        const p = pos.get(id) || { x: 40, y: 40, w: 170, h: 60 };
        const style = drawioStyleFor(n);
        cells.push(
          `        <mxCell id="n_${xmlEscape(id)}" value="${xmlEscape(n.label)}" style="${style}" vertex="1" parent="1">\n` +
          `          <mxGeometry x="${Math.round(p.x)}" y="${Math.round(p.y)}" width="${p.w}" height="${p.h}" as="geometry" />\n` +
          `        </mxCell>`);
      }
      edges.forEach((e, idx) => {
        if (!nodes.has(e.from) || !nodes.has(e.to)) return;
        const style = 'edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;endArrow=block;';
        cells.push(
          `        <mxCell id="e_${idx}" value="${xmlEscape(e.label || '')}" style="${style}" edge="1" parent="1" source="n_${xmlEscape(e.from)}" target="n_${xmlEscape(e.to)}">\n` +
          `          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />\n` +
          `        </mxCell>`);
      });
      return `<mxfile host="app.diagrams.net" agent="diagram-pipeline" version="24.0.0">\n` +
        `  <diagram id="diagram-pipeline" name="Page-1">\n` +
        `    <mxGraphModel dx="900" dy="600" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1169" pageHeight="826" math="0" shadow="0">\n` +
        `      <root>\n        <mxCell id="0" />\n        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />\n` +
        cells.join('\n') + '\n      </root>\n    </mxGraphModel>\n  </diagram>\n</mxfile>\n';
    }

    // ---------- Flow register ----------
    function flowChains(graph, cap = 500) {
      const { nodes, edges } = graph;
      const adj = new Map([...nodes.keys()].map((id) => [id, []]));
      const indeg = new Map([...nodes.keys()].map((id) => [id, 0]));
      const outdeg = new Map([...nodes.keys()].map((id) => [id, 0]));
      edges.forEach((e) => {
        if (!nodes.has(e.from) || !nodes.has(e.to)) return;
        adj.get(e.from).push({ to: e.to, label: e.label });
        outdeg.set(e.from, outdeg.get(e.from) + 1);
        indeg.set(e.to, indeg.get(e.to) + 1);
      });
      const sources = [...nodes.keys()].filter((id) => indeg.get(id) === 0 && outdeg.get(id) > 0);
      const chains = []; let truncated = false;
      const walk = (id, pathNodes, pathEdges) => {
        if (chains.length >= cap) { truncated = true; return; }
        const outs = adj.get(id) || [];
        if (outs.length === 0) { if (pathEdges.length) chains.push([...pathEdges]); return; }
        for (const o of outs) {
          if (pathNodes.has(o.to)) { chains.push([...pathEdges, { from: id, to: o.to, label: o.label }]); continue; }
          pathNodes.add(o.to);
          walk(o.to, pathNodes, [...pathEdges, { from: id, to: o.to, label: o.label }]);
          pathNodes.delete(o.to);
        }
      };
      for (const s of sources) { if (chains.length >= cap) { truncated = true; break; } walk(s, new Set([s]), []); }
      if (chains.length === 0) edges.forEach((e) => { if (nodes.has(e.from) && nodes.has(e.to)) chains.push([{ from: e.from, to: e.to, label: e.label }]); });
      return { chains, truncated };
    }
    function buildRegister(graph, refMap, typeMap) {
      const { nodes } = graph;
      const labelOf = (id) => (nodes.get(id)?.label || id);
      const ref = (label) => refMap[label.toLowerCase().trim()] || { database: '', platform: '' };
      const typ = (label) => (typeMap && typeMap[label.toLowerCase().trim()]) || '';
      const { chains, truncated } = flowChains(graph);
      const flowRows = [];
      chains.forEach((hops, ci) => hops.forEach((h, hi) => {
        const fromL = labelOf(h.from), toL = labelOf(h.to), fr = ref(fromL), tr = ref(toL);
        flowRows.push([`F${ci + 1}`, hi + 1, fromL, typ(fromL), h.label || '', toL, typ(toL), fr.database, fr.platform, tr.database, tr.platform]);
      }));
      const hopRows = graph.edges.filter((e) => nodes.has(e.from) && nodes.has(e.to)).map((e) => {
        const fromL = labelOf(e.from), toL = labelOf(e.to), fr = ref(fromL), tr = ref(toL);
        return [fromL, typ(fromL), e.label || '', toL, typ(toL), fr.database, fr.platform, tr.database, tr.platform];
      });
      return { flowRows, hopRows, truncated, chainCount: chains.length };
    }
    // Complete label→type map: the grid's explicit choice wins, else inferred.
    function fullTypeMap(graph, gridTypes) {
      const map = {};
      for (const n of graph.nodes.values()) { const k = n.label.toLowerCase().trim(); map[k] = gridTypes[k] || inferType(n); }
      return map;
    }

    function currentGraph() { return parseMermaid($('code').value); }

    // ---------- STEP 1: image upload ----------
    // The vision API takes PNG/JPG/WebP/GIF — not SVG. So an uploaded SVG is
    // rasterised to PNG in-browser (canvas) before it's sent. No server change.
    function isSvgFile(f) { return f.type === 'image/svg+xml' || /\.svg$/i.test(f.name || ''); }
    function svgIntrinsicSize(text) {
      const head = text.slice(0, (text.indexOf('>', text.indexOf('<svg')) + 1) || 600);
      const num = (re) => { const m = re.exec(head); return m && !/%/.test(m[1]) ? parseFloat(m[1]) : 0; };
      let w = num(/\bwidth\s*=\s*"([^"]+)"/i), h = num(/\bheight\s*=\s*"([^"]+)"/i);
      if (!w || !h) { const vb = /\bviewBox\s*=\s*"([-\d.\s,]+)"/i.exec(head); if (vb) { const p = vb[1].trim().split(/[\s,]+/).map(Number); if (p.length === 4) { w = w || p[2]; h = h || p[3]; } } }
      if (!w || w > 100000) w = 1200; if (!h || h > 100000) h = 800;
      return { w: Math.round(w), h: Math.round(h) };
    }
    function ensureSvgSize(text, w, h) {
      return text.replace(/<svg\b([^>]*)>/i, (m, attrs) => { let a = attrs; if (!/\bwidth\s*=/.test(a)) a += ` width="${w}"`; if (!/\bheight\s*=/.test(a)) a += ` height="${h}"`; return `<svg${a}>`; });
    }
    async function svgToPngB64(f) {
      const text = await f.text();
      const { w, h } = svgIntrinsicSize(text);
      const scale = Math.min(Math.max(1600 / Math.max(w, h), 1), 4); // upscale small SVGs for legible OCR, cap 4×
      const tw = Math.min(Math.round(w * scale), 4000), th = Math.min(Math.round(h * scale), 4000);
      const url = URL.createObjectURL(new Blob([ensureSvgSize(text, w, h)], { type: 'image/svg+xml' }));
      try {
        const img = await new Promise((res, rej) => { const i = new Image(); i.onload = () => res(i); i.onerror = () => rej(new Error('Could not render the SVG.')); i.src = url; });
        const canvas = document.createElement('canvas'); canvas.width = tw; canvas.height = th;
        const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d'); ctx.fillStyle = '#ffffff'; ctx.fillRect(0, 0, tw, th); ctx.drawImage(img, 0, 0, tw, th);
        let dataUrl;
        try { dataUrl = canvas.toDataURL('image/png'); }
        catch (_) { throw new Error('This SVG embeds external images or HTML the browser can’t rasterise — export it as PNG and upload that instead.'); }
        return dataUrl.split(',')[1];
      } finally { URL.revokeObjectURL(url); }
    }
    async function imagePayload(f) {
      if (isSvgFile(f)) return { b64: await svgToPngB64(f), mediaType: 'image/png' };
      const dataUrl = await new Promise((res, rej) => { const r = new FileReader(); r.onload = () => res(r.result); r.onerror = rej; r.readAsDataURL(f); });
      return { b64: String(dataUrl).split(',')[1], mediaType: f.type || 'image/png' };
    }

    // ---------- structured-SVG extraction (lossless, no AI) ----------
    // mermaid renders and draw.io exports already encode the graph. Read it
    // straight from the SVG instead of rasterising + re-running vision.
    function decodeEntities(s) { const t = document.createElement('textarea'); t.innerHTML = s; return t.value; }
    function stripHtml(s) { return decodeEntities(String(s)).replace(/<[^>]+>/g, ' ').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim(); }
    function cleanText(s) { return String(s || '').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim(); }

    function graphToMermaid(graph) {
      const esc = (s) => String(s).replace(/"/g, "'").replace(/[\[\]{}()<>|]/g, ' ').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();
      const SHP = { rect: (l) => `["${l}"]`, cylinder: (l) => `[("${l}")]`, diamond: (l) => `{"${l}"}`, hexagon: (l) => `{{"${l}"}}`, stadium: (l) => `(["${l}"])` };
      const idMap = new Map(); let k = 0;
      const safe = (id) => { if (!idMap.has(id)) idMap.set(id, /^[A-Za-z][\w]*$/.test(id) ? id : 'N' + (k++)); return idMap.get(id); };
      const lines = ['flowchart ' + (graph.direction || 'LR')];
      for (const [id, n] of graph.nodes) lines.push(`  ${safe(id)}${(SHP[n.shape] || SHP.rect)(esc(n.label))}`);
      for (const e of graph.edges) { const lbl = e.label ? `|"${esc(e.label)}"|` : ''; lines.push(`  ${safe(e.from)} -->${lbl} ${safe(e.to)}`); }
      return lines.join('\n');
    }

    function extractDrawioContent(text) {
      const m = /<svg\b[^>]*\bcontent="([^"]*)"/i.exec(text);
      if (!m) return null;
      const xml = decodeEntities(m[1]);
      return /mxGraphModel|mxfile/i.test(xml) ? xml : null;
    }
    function mxShape(style) {
      const s = (style || '').toLowerCase();
      if (/cylinder/.test(s)) return 'cylinder';
      if (/rhombus/.test(s)) return 'diamond';
      if (/hexagon/.test(s)) return 'hexagon';
      return 'rect';
    }
    function mxToGraph(xml) {
      const doc = new DOMParser().parseFromString(xml, 'text/xml');
      if (doc.querySelector('parsererror')) return null;
      const nodes = new Map(), edges = [];
      for (const c of doc.querySelectorAll('mxCell')) {
        if (c.getAttribute('vertex') === '1') {
          const id = c.getAttribute('id'); if (!id) continue;
          const label = stripHtml(c.getAttribute('value') || '');
          nodes.set(id, { id, label: label || id, shape: mxShape(c.getAttribute('style')) });
        }
      }
      for (const c of doc.querySelectorAll('mxCell')) {
        if (c.getAttribute('edge') === '1') {
          const from = c.getAttribute('source'), to = c.getAttribute('target');
          if (from && to && nodes.has(from) && nodes.has(to)) edges.push({ from, to, label: stripHtml(c.getAttribute('value') || '') });
        }
      }
      return nodes.size ? { direction: 'LR', nodes, edges } : null;
    }

    function nodeLabelOf(el) {
      const ts = [...el.querySelectorAll('tspan')];
      if (ts.length) return cleanText(ts.map((t) => t.textContent.trim()).filter(Boolean).join(' '));
      return cleanText(el.textContent);
    }
    function mermaidSvgToGraph(text) {
      const doc = new DOMParser().parseFromString(text, 'image/svg+xml');
      if (doc.querySelector('parsererror')) return null;
      const nodes = new Map();
      for (const el of doc.querySelectorAll('[data-id]')) {
        if (!/\bnode\b/.test(el.getAttribute('class') || '')) continue;
        const id = el.getAttribute('data-id'); if (!id || nodes.has(id)) continue;
        const label = nodeLabelOf(el);
        nodes.set(id, { id, label: label || id, shape: 'rect' });
      }
      if (!nodes.size) return null;
      const labels = [...doc.querySelectorAll('.edgeLabel')].map((e) => cleanText(e.textContent));
      const edges = []; let i = 0;
      for (const p of doc.querySelectorAll('[class*="flowchart-link"]')) {
        const cls = p.getAttribute('class') || '';
        const ls = /LS-([A-Za-z0-9_]+)/.exec(cls), le = /LE-([A-Za-z0-9_]+)/.exec(cls);
        if (ls && le && nodes.has(ls[1]) && nodes.has(le[1])) edges.push({ from: ls[1], to: le[1], label: labels[i] || '' });
        i++;
      }
      return { direction: 'LR', nodes, edges };
    }
    function structuredSvgToGraph(text) {
      try {
        const dio = extractDrawioContent(text);
        if (dio) { const g = mxToGraph(dio); if (g) return g; }
        if (/aria-roledescription="[^"]*(flowchart|graph)/i.test(text) || /flowchart-link/.test(text)) return mermaidSvgToGraph(text);
      } catch (_) { /* fall back to vision */ }
      return null;
    }
    function selFile(f) {
      if (f.size > 6 * 1024 * 1024) { $('status').textContent = 'Image too large (max 6 MB).'; return; }
      file = f; $('thumb').src = URL.createObjectURL(f); $('previmg').hidden = false; $('go').disabled = false; $('status').textContent = 'Ready: ' + f.name + (isSvgFile(f) ? ' (SVG — will be rasterised)' : '');
    }
    $('file').addEventListener('change', (e) => { const f = e.target.files?.[0]; if (f) selFile(f); });
    const dz = $('drop');
    dz.addEventListener('dragover', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); dz.classList.add('drag'); });
    dz.addEventListener('dragleave', () => dz.classList.remove('drag'));
    dz.addEventListener('drop', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); dz.classList.remove('drag'); const f = e.dataTransfer?.files?.[0]; if (f) selFile(f); });
    $('go').addEventListener('click', async () => {
      if (!file) return; $('go').disabled = true;
      try {
        // A structured SVG (mermaid render / draw.io export) carries the graph
        // verbatim — extract it directly and skip the lossy vision round-trip.
        if (isSvgFile(file)) {
          const text = await file.text();
          const g = structuredSvgToGraph(text);
          if (g && g.nodes.size) {
            $('code').value = graphToMermaid(g);
            await render();
            $('status').textContent = `Extracted ${g.nodes.size} node${g.nodes.size === 1 ? '' : 's'} & ${g.edges.length} edge${g.edges.length === 1 ? '' : 's'} directly from the SVG — no AI needed.`;
            return;
          }
          $('status').textContent = 'No embedded structure — rasterising SVG for vision AI…';
        } else {
          $('status').textContent = 'Reading the diagram with vision AI…';
        }
        const { b64, mediaType } = await imagePayload(file);
        $('status').textContent = 'Reading the diagram with vision AI…';
        const resp = await fetch(WORKER + '/image-to-mermaid', { method: 'POST', headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }, body: JSON.stringify({ image: b64, mediaType }) });
        const j = await resp.json();
        if (!resp.ok) throw new Error(j.error || ('HTTP ' + resp.status));
        $('code').value = (j.mermaid || '').trim();
        await render();
        $('status').textContent = 'Done — review the Mermaid in step 2.';
      } catch (e) { $('status').textContent = 'Error: ' + (e.message || e); } finally { $('go').disabled = false; }
    });

    // ---------- STEP 2: mermaid preview ----------
    async function render() {
      const code = $('code').value.trim(); if (!code) { $('preview').innerHTML = ''; return; }
      try { const mer = await mermaidLib(); const { svg } = await mer.render('m' + Math.random().toString(36).slice(2), code); $('preview').innerHTML = svg; }
      catch (e) { $('preview').innerHTML = `<div class="err">Diagram didn't parse — edit the code and re-render.<br><small>${(e.message || e).toString().replace(/</g, '&lt;').slice(0, 200)}</small></div>`; }
    }
    $('render').addEventListener('click', render);
    $('copyM').addEventListener('click', async () => { try { await navigator.clipboard.writeText($('code').value); $('status').textContent = 'Mermaid copied.'; } catch { $('status').textContent = 'Copy failed.'; } });
    $('dlM').addEventListener('click', () => download($('code').value, 'diagram.mmd', 'text/plain'));
    $('sample').addEventListener('click', () => {
      $('code').value = `flowchart LR\n  CRM[Salesforce CRM] -->|API/REST| ESB[MuleSoft ESB]\n  ESB -->|OData| ERP[SAP S/4HANA]\n  ERP -->|ETL/ELT| DW[(Snowflake)]\n  DW -->|SQL| BI[Power BI]\n  CRM -->|Kafka stream| DW`;
      render(); $('status').textContent = 'Sample loaded.';
    });

    // ---------- STEP 3: draw.io ----------
    function genDrawio() {
      const g = currentGraph();
      if (g.nodes.size === 0) { $('statusD').textContent = 'No nodes found — add a flowchart in step 2.'; return; }
      typeLookup = fullTypeMap(g, typeMapFromGrid()); // pick up any Type overrides from step 4
      lastXml = toDrawio(g, layout(g));
      const ta = $('drawioXml'); ta.hidden = false; ta.value = lastXml;
      $('dlDrawio').disabled = false; $('openDrawio').disabled = false; $('copyDrawio').disabled = false;
      $('statusD').textContent = `${g.nodes.size} shapes · ${g.edges.length} connections · ${drawioScheme} colours.`;
    }
    $('genDrawio').addEventListener('click', genDrawio);
    $('scheme').addEventListener('change', (e) => { drawioScheme = e.target.value; if (lastXml) genDrawio(); });
    $('dlDrawio').addEventListener('click', () => download(lastXml, 'diagram.drawio', 'application/xml'));
    $('copyDrawio').addEventListener('click', async () => { try { await navigator.clipboard.writeText(lastXml); $('statusD').textContent = 'XML copied.'; } catch { $('statusD').textContent = 'Copy failed.'; } });
    $('openDrawio').addEventListener('click', () => {
      if (!lastXml) return;
      window.open('https://app.diagrams.net/?title=diagram.drawio#R' + encodeURIComponent(lastXml), '_blank', 'noopener,noreferrer');
    });

    // ---------- STEP 4: reference grid + xlsx ----------
    function loadRef() { try { return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(REF_KEY) || '[]'); } catch { return []; } }
    function saveRef(rows) { try { localStorage.setItem(REF_KEY, JSON.stringify(rows)); } catch (_) {} }
    function readGrid() {
      return [...$('refBody').querySelectorAll('tr')].map((tr) => ({
        application: tr.querySelector('.c-app').value.trim(),
        type: tr.querySelector('.c-type').value,
        database: tr.querySelector('.c-db').value.trim(),
        platform: tr.querySelector('.c-plat').value.trim(),
      })).filter((r) => r.application || r.database || r.platform);
    }
    function refMapFromGrid() {
      const map = {};
      for (const r of readGrid()) if (r.application) map[r.application.toLowerCase().trim()] = { database: r.database, platform: r.platform };
      return map;
    }
    function typeMapFromGrid() {
      const map = {};
      for (const r of readGrid()) if (r.application && r.type) map[r.application.toLowerCase().trim()] = r.type;
      return map;
    }
    function rowEl(r = { application: '', type: '', database: '', platform: '' }) {
      const tr = document.createElement('tr');
      const opts = ['<option value="">(auto)</option>'].concat(NODE_TYPES.map((t) => `<option value="${t}"${r.type === t ? ' selected' : ''}>${t}</option>`)).join('');
      tr.innerHTML =
        `<td><input class="c-app" value="${escAttr(r.application)}" placeholder="Node" /></td>` +
        `<td><select class="c-type">${opts}</select></td>` +
        `<td><input class="c-db" value="${escAttr(r.database)}" placeholder="Database" /></td>` +
        `<td><input class="c-plat" value="${escAttr(r.platform)}" placeholder="Platform" /></td>` +
        `<td><button class="btn sm danger rm" title="Remove">✕</button></td>`;
      tr.querySelector('.rm').addEventListener('click', () => { tr.remove(); persistGrid(); });
      tr.querySelectorAll('input, select').forEach((el) => el.addEventListener('input', persistGrid));
      return tr;
    }
    function persistGrid() { saveRef(readGrid()); updateRefCount(); }
    function updateRefCount() { const n = readGrid().length; $('refCount').textContent = n ? `(${n})` : ''; }
    function renderGrid(rows) { const b = $('refBody'); b.innerHTML = ''; rows.forEach((r) => b.appendChild(rowEl(r))); if (!rows.length) b.appendChild(rowEl()); updateRefCount(); }

    function seedFromDiagram() {
      const g = currentGraph();
      const byLabel = new Map();
      for (const n of g.nodes.values()) if (!byLabel.has(n.label)) byLabel.set(n.label, n);
      if (!byLabel.size) { $('statusX').textContent = 'No nodes found in the diagram yet.'; return; }
      const existing = readGrid();
      const have = new Set(existing.map((r) => r.application.toLowerCase().trim()));
      let added = 0;
      for (const [label, node] of byLabel) if (!have.has(label.toLowerCase().trim())) { existing.push({ application: label, type: inferType(node), database: '', platform: '' }); added++; }
      renderGrid(existing); persistGrid();
      $('statusX').textContent = added ? `Added ${added} node${added === 1 ? '' : 's'} (types auto-classified — adjust any below).` : 'All diagram nodes already listed.';
    }
    $('seedRef').addEventListener('click', seedFromDiagram);
    $('addRow').addEventListener('click', () => { $('refBody').appendChild(rowEl()); });
    $('clearRef').addEventListener('click', () => { if (confirm('Clear the node reference table?')) { renderGrid([]); persistGrid(); } });

    $('exportRefCsv').addEventListener('click', () => {
      const rows = [['Node', 'Type', 'Database', 'Technology Platform'], ...readGrid().map((r) => [r.application, r.type, r.database, r.platform])];
      download(rows.map(csvLine).join('\r\n'), 'node-reference.csv', 'text/csv');
    });
    $('refCsv').addEventListener('change', async (e) => {
      const f = e.target.files?.[0]; if (!f) return;
      const text = await f.text();
      const rows = parseCsv(text);
      const hasHeader = rows.length && /node|application/i.test(rows[0][0] || '');
      // 4-col (Node,Type,Database,Platform) vs legacy 3-col (App,Database,Platform)
      const typed = hasHeader ? /type/i.test(rows[0][1] || '') : true;
      const start = hasHeader ? 1 : 0;
      const parsed = rows.slice(start).filter((r) => r.some((c) => c && c.trim())).map((r) => typed
        ? { application: (r[0] || '').trim(), type: (r[1] || '').trim(), database: (r[2] || '').trim(), platform: (r[3] || '').trim() }
        : { application: (r[0] || '').trim(), type: '', database: (r[1] || '').trim(), platform: (r[2] || '').trim() });
      renderGrid(parsed); persistGrid();
      $('statusX').textContent = `Imported ${parsed.length} row${parsed.length === 1 ? '' : 's'} from CSV.`;
      e.target.value = '';
    });

    $('exportXlsx').addEventListener('click', async () => {
      const g = currentGraph();
      if (g.edges.length === 0) { $('statusX').textContent = 'No connections to export — add a flowchart in step 2.'; return; }
      $('statusX').textContent = 'Building workbook…';
      try {
        const XLSX = await loadXlsx();
        const rmap = refMapFromGrid();
        const tmap = fullTypeMap(g, typeMapFromGrid());
        const reg = buildRegister(g, rmap, tmap);
        const wb = XLSX.utils.book_new();

        if ($('optChains').checked) {
          const flowHead = ['Flow ID', 'Hop #', 'From Application', 'From Type', 'Interface Mechanism', 'To Application', 'To Type', 'From Database', 'From Platform', 'To Database', 'To Platform'];
          const ws = XLSX.utils.aoa_to_sheet([flowHead, ...reg.flowRows]);
          ws['!cols'] = [{ wch: 8 }, { wch: 6 }, { wch: 24 }, { wch: 16 }, { wch: 20 }, { wch: 24 }, { wch: 16 }, { wch: 18 }, { wch: 18 }, { wch: 18 }, { wch: 18 }];
          XLSX.utils.book_append_sheet(wb, ws, 'Flow Register');
        }

        const hopHead = ['From Application', 'From Type', 'Interface Mechanism', 'To Application', 'To Type', 'From Database', 'From Platform', 'To Database', 'To Platform'];
        const wsH = XLSX.utils.aoa_to_sheet([hopHead, ...reg.hopRows]);
        wsH['!cols'] = [{ wch: 24 }, { wch: 16 }, { wch: 20 }, { wch: 24 }, { wch: 16 }, { wch: 18 }, { wch: 18 }, { wch: 18 }, { wch: 18 }];
        XLSX.utils.book_append_sheet(wb, wsH, 'Hops');

        const nodeHead = ['Node', 'Type', 'Database', 'Technology Platform'];
        const seen = new Set(), nodeRows = [];
        for (const n of g.nodes.values()) { const k = n.label.toLowerCase().trim(); if (seen.has(k)) continue; seen.add(k); const r = rmap[k] || {}; nodeRows.push([n.label, tmap[k] || '', r.database || '', r.platform || '']); }
        const wsA = XLSX.utils.aoa_to_sheet([nodeHead, ...nodeRows]);
        wsA['!cols'] = [{ wch: 28 }, { wch: 18 }, { wch: 20 }, { wch: 22 }];
        XLSX.utils.book_append_sheet(wb, wsA, 'Nodes');

        // Build bytes and download via our own helper — more reliable across
        // browsers than SheetJS writeFile's internal download.
        const out = XLSX.write(wb, { type: 'array', bookType: 'xlsx' });
        download(out, 'flow-register.xlsx', 'application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet');
        $('statusX').textContent = `Exported ${reg.hopRows.length} hop${reg.hopRows.length === 1 ? '' : 's'}` +
          ($('optChains').checked ? ` · ${reg.chainCount} chain${reg.chainCount === 1 ? '' : 's'}${reg.truncated ? ' (capped)' : ''}` : '') + '.';
      } catch (e) { $('statusX').textContent = 'Export failed: ' + (e.message || e); }
    });

    // ---------- helpers ----------
    function escAttr(s) { return String(s).replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/"/g, '&quot;').replace(/</g, '&lt;'); }
    function csvLine(arr) { return arr.map((v) => { v = String(v ?? ''); return /[",\r\n]/.test(v) ? '"' + v.replace(/"/g, '""') + '"' : v; }).join(','); }
    function parseCsv(text) {
      const rows = []; let row = [], cur = '', q = false;
      for (let i = 0; i < text.length; i++) {
        const ch = text[i];
        if (q) { if (ch === '"') { if (text[i + 1] === '"') { cur += '"'; i++; } else q = false; } else cur += ch; }
        else if (ch === '"') q = true;
        else if (ch === ',') { row.push(cur); cur = ''; }
        else if (ch === '\n') { row.push(cur); rows.push(row); row = []; cur = ''; }
        else if (ch === '\r') { /* skip */ }
        else cur += ch;
      }
      if (cur.length || row.length) { row.push(cur); rows.push(row); }
      return rows;
    }
    function download(content, name, type) {
      const blob = new Blob([content], { type }); const a = document.createElement('a');
      a.href = URL.createObjectURL(blob); a.download = name; a.click(); setTimeout(() => URL.revokeObjectURL(a.href), 15000);
    }
    function loadXlsx() {
      return new Promise((res, rej) => {
        if (window.XLSX) return res(window.XLSX);
        const s = document.createElement('script');
        s.src = 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/xlsx/0.18.5/xlsx.full.min.js';
        s.onload = () => res(window.XLSX); s.onerror = () => rej(new Error('Could not load the spreadsheet library.'));
        document.head.appendChild(s);
      });
    }

    // init
    renderGrid(loadRef());
  </script>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .tool { max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .thead { margin-bottom: 18px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding-bottom: 12px; }
  .kick { font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-fg-subtle); font-weight: 600; }
  .thead h1 { margin-top: 4px; font-size: 28px; line-height: 1.15; }
  .sub { margin-top: 8px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--color-fg-muted); max-width: 70ch; }
  .back { display: inline-block; margin-top: 10px; color: var(--color-fg-muted); text-decoration: none; font-size: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 6px 10px; }
  .back:hover { color: var(--color-fg); border-color: var(--color-accent); }

  .step { border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 12px; background: var(--color-bg-elevated); padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .step-h { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .step-h .n { display: inline-grid; place-items: center; width: 22px; height: 22px; border-radius: 999px; background: var(--color-accent); color: var(--color-accent-fg); font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; }
  .muted2 { color: var(--color-fg-muted); font-weight: 400; font-size: 13px; }
  .sub-h { font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--color-fg-muted); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .hint { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--color-fg-muted); margin: 6px 0 12px; line-height: 1.5; }
  .hint code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; background: var(--color-bg); padding: 1px 4px; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }

  .drop { border: 2px dashed var(--color-border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; text-align: center; position: relative; margin-bottom: 12px; cursor: pointer; background: var(--color-bg); }
  .drop.drag { border-color: var(--color-accent); }
  .drop input[type=file] { position: absolute; inset: 0; opacity: 0; cursor: pointer; }
  .dl { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; } .ds { font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-fg-muted); }
  .preview-img { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 10px; } .preview-img img { max-height: 180px; max-width: 100%; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px; }

  .status { font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-fg-muted); }
  .grid2 { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 14px; }
  .col { min-width: 0; }
  .code { width: 100%; min-height: 300px; resize: vertical; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 10px; background: var(--color-bg); color: var(--color-fg); padding: 12px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; }
  .mono-sm { min-height: 200px; font-size: 11.5px; margin-top: 10px; }
  .preview { min-height: 300px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 10px; background: #fff; padding: 12px; overflow: auto; display: grid; place-items: center; }
  .preview :global(svg) { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .err { color: #b94a48; font-size: 13px; text-align: center; }

  .row { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; margin-top: 4px; }
  .row.tight { margin-bottom: 8px; }
